# mstack CI & quality gates

## Goals

- **Fast feedback**: fail on the **cheapest** signal first when it catches most issues (format/lint before heavy e2e), unless the repo already orders jobs intentionally.
- **Deterministic**: pinned tool versions or lockfiles; avoid “latest” floating tags in CI without a policy.
- **Secrets**: use platform secret stores; never echo tokens; mask outputs; least privilege tokens.

## Changing rules or checks

- Do **not** disable lint rules, lower coverage thresholds, or remove typecheck steps to “go green” **without explicit user consent** — prefer fixing code or scoped overrides with rationale.
- If splitting jobs, keep **artifact** or **cache** keys aligned with lockfiles.

## Monorepos

- Use existing **task runner** patterns (`turbo`, `nx`, workspace filters) instead of ad hoc `cd` spaghetti; match cache configuration to the host (GitHub Actions cache, etc.).

## When skipping checks

- Document **why** in the PR or commit message (e.g. emergency hotfix with follow-up issue); prefer feature flags or branch protections over permanent skips.

## Docs

- If CI commands change, update **contributor docs** (`README`, `CONTRIBUTING`) in the same change when reasonable.
